data.enText: to print more copies of a book, an article, etc. with few or no changes
an act of printing more copies of a book because all the others have been sold
a book that has been reprinted

simple_means.memory_skill: re 一再，重新 + print 出版 → 再版

tr: a separately printed article that originally appeared in a larger publication
a publication (such as a book) that is reprinted without changes or editing and offered again for sale

example: They never reprinted the famous treatise

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /ˌriː'prɪnt/. The noun is pronounced /'riːprɪnt/. 动词读作/ˌriː'prɪnt/。名词读作/'riːprɪnt/。

value.def: If a book is reprinted, further copies of it are printed when all the other ones have been sold.

example.ex: It remained an exceptionally rare book until it was reprinted in 1918.
example.tran: 在1918年再版之前，这本书一直非常罕见。

value.def: A reprint is a process in which new copies of a book or article are printed because all the other ones have been sold.

example.ex: Demand picked up and a reprint was required last November.
example.tran: 由于需求量上升，去年11月，再版已是势在必行。

value.def: A reprint is a new copy of a book or article, printed because all the other ones have been sold or because minor changes have been made to the original.
